cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and person re-identification. The use of Gaussian distributions and Symmetric Positive Definite (SPD) matrix manifold also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves feature normalization methods, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of hierarchical covariance descriptors and the development of novel descriptors could also suggest that it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
